.2307/1312899</a><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">11 March</span> 2013</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=BioScience&amp;rft.atitle=Producing+a+great+textbook+with+the+help+of+a+developmental+editor&amp;rft.volume=46&amp;rft.issue=9&amp;rft.pages=691-693&amp;rft.date=1996&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.2307%2F1312899&amp;rft.aulast=Hart&amp;rft.aufirst=Stephen&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fbioscience.oxfordjournals.org%2Fcontent%2F46%2F9%2F691&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ADevelopmental+editing\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-UChicago-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-UChicago_5-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Germano, William (2008). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.press.uchicago.edu/Misc/Chicago/288447.html\"><i>Getting it published: a guide for scholars and anyone else serious about serious books</i></a>. Chicago: University of Chicago Press. pp.&#160;5\u201328. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780226288529\" title=\"Special:BookSources/9780226288529\">9780226288529</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Getting+it+published%3A+a+guide+for+scholars+and+anyone+else+serious+about+serious+books&amp;rft.place=Chicago&amp;rft.pages=5-28&amp;rft.pub=University+of+Chicago+Press&amp;rft.date=2008&amp;rft.isbn=9780226288529&amp;rft.aulast=Germano&amp;rft.aufirst=William&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.press.uchicago.edu%2FMisc%2FChicago%2F288447.html&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ADevelopmental+editing\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-IntBookPub-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-IntBookPub_6-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Altbach, Philip Gabriel; Hoshino, ES (eds) (1995). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=nkrGLRvKWpwC&amp;pg=PA91\"><i>International book publishing: an encyclopedia</i></a>. New York: Routledge. p.&#160;91. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/1884964168\" title=\"Special:BookSources/1884964168\">1884964168</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=International+book+publishing%3A+an+encyclopedia&amp;rft.place=New+York&amp;rft.pages=91&amp;rft.pub=Routledge&amp;rft.date=1995&amp;rft.isbn=1884964168&amp;rft.aulast=Altbach&amp;rft.aufirst=Philip+Gabriel&amp;rft.au=Hoshino%2C+ES+%28eds%29&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DnkrGLRvKWpwC%26pg%3DPA91&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ADevelopmental+editing\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span><span class=\"citation-comment\" style=\"display:none; color:#33aa33; margin-left:0.3em\">CS1 maint: Extra text: authors list (<a href=\"/wiki/Category:CS1_maint:_Extra_text:_authors_list\" title=\"Category:CS1 maint: Extra text: authors list\">link</a>) </span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-CollabWrite-7\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-CollabWrite_7-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-CollabWrite_7-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Matarese, Valerie (2013). <i>Collaborative research writing: developmental editing with an underlying educational vein. In: Matarese, V. (ed) Supporting research